# A system of [[romanization]] (phonetic notation and transliteration to roman script) for [[Mandarin]] that is used in the [[People's Republic of China|People’s Republic of China]]. It helps with pronouncing Chinese characters. Consists of over 70 irregular “[[sounds]]” (not including accents) of [[vowel|vowels]], [[consonant]]s, and [[sounds]] that are irregular. It uses four different accents for each [[vowel]]: ā, á, ǎ, à, but sometimes the tones are represented by numbers <sup>1 2 3 4</sup> (e.g., pīnyīn or pin<sup>1</sup>yin<sup>1</sup>).

